                        <h2 class="title">How Itemized Invoice works</h2>
                        <ol type="1" class="list level-3">
                            <li class="item">
                                <p class="desc">
                                    <strong class="font-semibold">Invoice Creation:</strong> Merchants can create invoices directly through the CCAvenue invoice solution. This involves providing details such as the amount due, description of goods or services, and any applicable taxes. The invoicing platform allows merchants to create Itemized as well as Quick Invoice depending upon the need of
                                    the hour.
                                </p>
                            </li>

                            <li class="item">
                                <p class="desc"><strong class="font-semibold">Generate Payment Link:</strong> Once the invoice is created, the system generates a unique payment link. This link is associated with the specific invoice and includes all relevant details. CCAvenue uses Tiny URL to ensure that links can be easily communicated through SMS.</p>
                            </li>

                            <li class="item">
                                <p class="desc"><strong class="font-semibold">Send Payment Link:</strong> Merchants can then share this payment link to their customers via email, SMS, or WhatsApp channel. The link directs the customer to a secure payment page where they can review the invoice amount and make a payment.</p>
                            </li>

                            <li class="item">
                                <p class="desc">
                                    <strong class="font-semibold">Customer Payment:</strong> The customer clicks the link, which takes them to a payment gateway page. They can pay using various methods such as credit/debit cards, UPI (Unified Payments Interface), net banking, or other supported payment methods configured against the merchant account. You can view all allocated payment options
                                    against your account through CCAvenue Merchant Accounting and Reporting System (M.A.R.S.)
                                </p>
                            </li>

                            <li class="item">
                                <p class="desc"><strong class="font-semibold">Confirmation and Notifications:</strong> After the payment is made, the merchant receives a notification, and the payment status is updated through CCAvenue Dynamic Event Notification (DEN). The customer typically also receives a confirmation receipt or email in case the feature has been enabled by the merchant.</p>
                            </li>

                            <li class="item">
                                <p class="desc"><strong class="font-semibold">Record Keeping:</strong> CCAvenue system records the payment and updates the invoice status, which helps in managing accounts and tracking receivables. Merchant can easily view the total invoices issued and paid by the customers.</p>
                            </li>

                            <li class="item">
                                <p class="desc"><strong class="font-semibold"> Customized Reports (MIS):</strong> CCAvenue Reporting Engine allows tailored reporting and analytical tools designed to meet the specific needs of merchants. Unlike standard MIS reports, which offer generic data, customised MIS provide insights that are more relevant and actionable for the individual business.</p>

